{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_53","type":"agent_message","text":"Adjusted the shared Docker-image task so it no longer uses Jackson just to parse `metadata/.../index.json`. In [ComputeAndPullAllowedDockerImagesTask.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6527-3d21225f/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/ComputeAndPullAllowedDockerImagesTask.java:148), index parsing now uses `JsonSlurper`, which removes the `ObjectMapper` runtime dependency from the failing `pullAllowedDockerImages` path and keeps the test-version resolution logic intact. I also added focused coverage in [ComputeAndPullAllowedDockerImagesTaskTests.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6527-3d21225f/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/ComputeAndPullAllowedDockerImagesTaskTests.java:18).\n\nVerified with:\n- `./gradlew -p tests/tck-build-logic test --tests org.graalvm.internal.tck.harness.tasks.ComputeAndPullAllowedDockerImagesTaskTests`\n- `GRAALVM_HOME=... GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=current-defaults JAVA_HOME=... ./gradlew testInfra -Pcoordinates=org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:12.1.0 -Pparallelism=1 --stacktrace`\n- fresh scratch run of the originally failing step: `GRADLE_USER_HOME=/tmp/... ./gradlew --no-daemon pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=io.grpc:grpc-core:1.81.0 --stacktrace`\n\nThere were pre-existing unrelated modified `stats/...` files in the worktree; I left those untouched."}}
